The article is a presidential order issued by President Joe Biden on January 20, 2021. The order focuses on implementing measures to halt the spread of COVID-19 in the United States. It emphasizes the importance of wearing masks, maintaining physical distance, and following other public health guidelines recommended by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). The order requires on-duty or on-site federal employees, federal contractors, and individuals in federal buildings and on federal lands to wear masks and adhere to public health measures. It also establishes the Safer Federal Workforce Task Force to provide ongoing guidance on the operation of the federal government during the pandemic. The order encourages cooperation between federal agencies and state, local, tribal, and territorial officials to promote mask-wearing and other public health measures. The Secretary of Health and Human Services is directed to develop a testing plan for the federal workforce, and the Director of the Office of Science and Technology Policy is instructed to assess research grants for studying effective mask-wearing and physical distancing policies. The order applies to federal employees, federal contractors, federal buildings, and federal lands.